cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with video analysis and action recognition, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves self-supervised learning and multi-task learning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using 3D convolutional networks, which are commonly used in multimedia analysis (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new motion representation, which involves learning internal motion dynamics, which could potentially fall under neural networks (cs.NE).
